The Permanent Secretary Special Duties Office (SDO), Office of the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (OSGF), Engr. Festus Yesufu Daudu, has decried the non-existence of local industries in Nasarawa despite the abundance of natural resources like salt and solid minerals in the state. Daudu expressed his displeasure during a courtesy call on the Emir of Nasarawa Eggon, Dr. Bala A. Angbazo in his palace recently. The spokesperson in his office, Mrs. Julie Osagie Jacobs, in a statement, quoted the permanent secretary as saying that the salt industry still remained untapped with local producers still using old methods of processing salt despite the availability of modern and effective methods. He said the industrialization plan of state governor Engr. Abdullahi Audu Sule, is a key towards bringing lasting peace to Nasarawa State and also is in line with President Muhammad Buhariâ€™s agenda of transforming the country to the next level of development.  Perm sec to states: Live in peace to attract investors FG, Nasarawa govt partner on industrialisation FG, Nasarawa to partner on industrialisation Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin